    "description": "\nWinter weather travel advisory in effect for today.\n\nWhat:\nTotal snowfall accumulations near 10 cm.\nReduced visibility in snow.\n\nWhen:\nThis morning through late this afternoon.\n\nAdditional information:\nAn Alberta clipper will bring snow over the area today. The heaviest snowfall is expected this morning. The snow will taper to light flurries this afternoon or evening.\n\n###\n\nTravel may be hazardous due to sudden changes in the weather.\n\nFor road conditions and other traveller information from the Ministry of Transportation, visit https://www.ontario.ca/511, https://www.twitter.com/511Ontario, or call 5-1-1.\n\nPlease continue to monitor alerts and forecasts issued by Environment Canada. To report severe weather, send an email to ONstorm@ec.gc.ca or post reports on X using #ONStorm.\n",
    "instruction": "\nBe prepared to adjust your driving with changing road conditions. If visibility is reduced while driving, turn on your lights and maintain a safe following distance.\n",
